  "bib_entries": {
    "118560513": {
      "title": "Metadynamics surfing on topology barriers: the CP N −1 case",
      "abstract": "In the continuum limit, QCD systems, investigated via numerical simulations, remain trapped in sectors of field space with fixed topological charge. As a consequence the numerical studies of physical quantities may give biased results. The same is true in the case of two dimensional CP(N-1) models. In this paper we show that Metadynamics, applied to CP(N-1), allows to bypass very efficiently this problem. In particular we show, for the first time, that we are able to reconstruct the free energy of the topological charge, F(Q), as a function of the coupling and of the volume. This is a very important physical quantity in studies of the dynamics of the theta-vacuum and of the axion. The method can be easily extended to QCD."
    }
  },
